⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Hudson Bee
node MSC · MSC · ⟦The Hudson Bee:MSC:fe8bc4⟧

WHO   — The Hudson Bee — the merchant-bee
WHAT  — The friendly merchant of the maze — where Milon spends the money he uncovers to buy items and power-ups for the long climb deeper in.
WHERE — MSC · Milon's Secret Castle  Framework inputs: Milon's Secret Castle (Hudson Soft, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a boy alone in a stolen castle needs more than bubbles; because the coins popped loose from the walls are worth nothing until there is somewhere to spend them; because every maze is kinder for a friendly face in it.
HOW   — By keeping shop — trading the money Milon finds for the items and power-ups that carry him further up Castle Garland.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Bring me the coins you find in the walls, brave boy, and I will trade you what you need to climb.

